```
lepax/
├── App.js
├── index.js
├── app.json
├── .env.example
├── firestore.rules
│
├── assets/
├── constants/
│   └── theme.js          brand colors + vibe config
├── firebase/
│   └── config.js         Firebase init (Auth + Firestore only)
├── context/
│   └── AuthContext.js    global auth + profile state
├── components/
│   ├── Avatar.js
│   └── VibeTag.js
├── navigation/
│   └── AppNavigator.js   stack + bottom tabs
└── screens/
    ├── AuthScreen.js         log in / sign up
    ├── HomeScreen.js         feed (Friends + Explore tabs) + FAB
    ├── PlanDetailScreen.js   view plan, join, fork
    ├── CreatePlanScreen.js   4-step plan creation
    ├── ProfileScreen.js      avatar upload, bio, stats
    └── FreeNowScreen.js      nudge free friends
```

---

## Firestore data model

| Collection | Doc ID | Key fields |
|---|---|---|
| `users` | `{uid}` | username, email, bio, avatarUrl, friends[], plansHosted, forksReceived |
| `plans` | auto | title, date, location, visibility, vibes[], itinerary[], hostId, hostUsername, joinedBy[], forks, createdAt |
| `nudges` | auto | fromUid, fromUsername, toUid, message, read, createdAt |

---

## Running locally

### 1. Clone the repo

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/lepax.git
cd lepax
```

### 2. Install dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

### 3. Set up Firebase

1. Go to [console.firebase.google.com](https://console.firebase.google.com)
2. Create a project → enable **Authentication** (Email/Password) and **Firestore**
3. Project Settings → Add a Web app → copy the config values

### 4. Set up Cloudinary

1. Sign up free at [cloudinary.com](https://cloudinary.com) — no credit card
2. Note your **Cloud Name** from the dashboard
3. Settings → Upload → Add upload preset → set to **Unsigned** → folder: `avatars`

### 5. Configure environment

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Fill in your values:

```env
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_APP_ID=

EXPO_PUBLIC_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=
EXPO_PUBLIC_CLOUDINARY_UPLOAD_PRESET=
```

### 6. Run

```bash
npx expo start
```

Scan the QR with **Expo Go** on your phone.

---

## What I learned

- Structuring a React Native app with real-time Firestore listeners
- Managing global auth state with React Context across a multi-screen app
- Integrating a third-party upload service (Cloudinary) without a backend
- Designing intentional anti-features — knowing what to leave out is as important as what to build
- Debugging Metro bundler path issues (lesson: never have spaces in your project folder path 😅)

